<div class="space-y-6">
  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mb-2">Respecting Reduced Motion Preferences</h3>
    <p class="mb-4">This example demonstrates how skeleton animations respect the user's reduced motion preferences:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mb-4">
      <li>Standard animation for users without motion preferences</li>
      <li>Reduced or no animation for users who prefer reduced motion</li>
      <li>CSS implementation using <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code> media query</li>
    </ul>
    
    <div class="p-4 border rounded-lg">
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div>
          <h4 class="text-md font-medium mb-2">Standard Animation</h4>
          <div class="space-y-2">
            <%= render Ui::SkeletonComponent.new(width: "100%", height: "20px") %>
            <%= render Ui::SkeletonComponent.new(width: "80%", height: "20px") %>
            <%= render Ui::SkeletonComponent.new(width: "60%", height: "20px") %>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h4 class="text-md font-medium mb-2">Reduced Motion (Simulated)</h4>
          <div class="space-y-2">
            <%= render Ui::SkeletonComponent.new(width: "100%", height: "20px", animate: false) %>
            <%= render Ui::SkeletonComponent.new(width: "80%", height: "20px", animate: false) %>
            <%= render Ui::SkeletonComponent.new(width: "60%", height: "20px", animate: false) %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mt-6">
        <h4 class="text-md font-medium mb-2">CSS Implementation</h4>
        <pre class="bg-muted p-2 rounded text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>@keyframes skeleton-pulse {
  0% { opacity: 0.5; }
  50% { opacity: 0.8; }
  100% { opacity: 0.5; }
}

.skeleton {
  animation: skeleton-pulse 2s ease-in-out infinite;
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .skeleton {
    animation: none;
  }
}</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mb-2">Alternative Loading Indicators</h3>
    <p class="mb-4">For users with reduced motion preferences, consider these alternatives:</p>
    
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="border rounded-lg p-4 [data-theme=dark]:border-gray-700">
        <h4 class="text-md font-medium mb-2">Static Indicators</h4>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <div class="w-4 h-4 rounded-full bg-primary"></div>
            <span>Loading content...</span>
          </div>
          
          <div class="space-y-2">
            <%= render Ui::SkeletonComponent.new(width: "100%", height: "20px", animate: false) %>
            <%= render Ui::SkeletonComponent.new(width: "80%", height: "20px", animate: false) %>
            <%= render Ui::SkeletonComponent.new(width: "60%", height: "20px", animate: false) %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="border rounded-lg p-4 [data-theme=dark]:border-gray-700">
        <h4 class="text-md font-medium mb-2">Text-Based Progress</h4>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <span>Loading content...</span>
            <span>60%</span>
          </div>
          
          <div class="w-full h-2 bg-muted rounded-full overflow-hidden">
            <div class="h-full bg-primary rounded-full" style="width: 60%"></div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="space-y-2">
            <%= render Ui::SkeletonComponent.new(width: "100%", height: "20px", animate: false) %>
            <%= render Ui::SkeletonComponent.new(width: "80%", height: "20px", animate: false) %>
            <%= render Ui::SkeletonComponent.new(width: "60%", height: "20px", animate: false) %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mb-2">Testing Reduced Motion</h3>
    <p class="mb-4">To test how components behave with reduced motion preferences:</p>
    <ol class="list-decimal pl-5">
      <li>In Chrome DevTools, open the Rendering tab (Esc > ... > Rendering)</li>
      <li>Enable "Emulate CSS media feature prefers-reduced-motion: reduce"</li>
      <li>Verify that animations are disabled or reduced</li>
      <li>Check that loading states are still clearly indicated</li>
      <li>Ensure all functionality remains accessible</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</div>